pr_review_comment_body:
Let's remove this temporary as part of this patch, that way you can use resultSetId insisde your function without a problem. E.g.:

```
function(resultSetId, index) {
   return resultSets[0].id == resultSetId ? index : null;
}
```

diff looks rather weird... All is happening here is the back-indent of the code (due to `VerifyOrExit`) at the top.
And replcating of the code block below with `SendSetPropertyResponse()` at `exit`:
```
if (errorCode == OT_ERROR_NONE)
{
    errorCode = HandleCommandPropertyGet(header, key)
}
else
{
   errorCode = SendLastStatus(header, ThreadErrorToSpinelStatus(errorCode));
}
```
